-- Survey — demonstrates map/reduce combinators.
-- Maps over a list of topics, then reduces findings into a summary.

## survey

  input param.topics : [str] required
  input param.question : str required

  -- Analyze each topic in parallel (map)
  map # analyze : llm over {{param.topics}} as topic
    system>
      You are a research analyst. Be concise and evidence-based.
    user>
      Analyze "{{topic}}" with respect to: {{param.question}}
      Provide 3-5 key findings.
    format> analysis
      { topic: str, findings: [str], confidence: number }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    keys_present(output, ["topic", "findings", "confidence"]);
    assert len(output.findings) >= 1;
    assert output.confidence >= 0;
    assert output.confidence <= 1;
    ```
  #/

  -- Combine all analyses into one summary (reduce)
  reduce # synthesize : llm over {{analyze.*}} as item with acc = "No findings yet."
    system>
      You synthesize research findings. Build on prior summary.
    context>
      Running summary so far:
      {{acc}}
    user>
      Incorporate these new findings:
      Topic: {{item.topic}}
      Findings: {{item.findings}}
      Confidence: {{item.confidence}}

      Update the running summary. Highlight agreements and conflicts.
    format> summary
      { summary: str, themes: [str], conflicts: [str] }
  #/

##/
